maintext:
Two killed, two injured in crash on I-26
Two people were killed and two others were injured when an SUV ran off the side of Interstate 26 and overturned early Sunday.
S.C. Highway Patrol Lance Cpl. Matt Southern said a Ford SUV driven by a North Charleston woman crashed off the right side of I-26 east at mile marker 188, a mile east of the Ridgeville exit. The wreck occurred at 12:10 a.m.
The front seat passenger and another passenger in the back seat were killed. Two juveniles in the back seat were injured and transported to an area hospital.
The Berkeley County Coronerâ€™s Office has not yet identified those killed in the crash.
Southern said the investigation is ongoing.
